'''Mahaney's theorem''' is a theorem in [[computational complexity theory]] proven by Stephen Mahaney that states that if any [[sparse language]] is [[NP-Complete]], then P=NP. Also, if there is a [[Turing reduction]] from an NP-complete sparse language to P, then the [[polynomial hierarchy|polynomial-time hierarchy]] collapses to [[‚àÜ_2]] (NP^{NP [logn]}).<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mahaney|first1=Stephen R.|title=Sparse complete sets for NP: Solution of a conjecture of Berman and Hartmanis|journal=Journal of Computer and System Sciences|date=October 1982|volume=25|issue=2|pages=130‚Äì143|doi=10.1016/0022-0000(82)90002-2|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022000082900022}}</ref>

